      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A robust, well-defended line of argument centers on national sovereignty and the rule of law. Stricter enforcement is not about hostility; it is a necessary function of any functioning nation-state to control its borders and manage its populace. Furthermore, increased funding directly addresses the security risks posed by illicit trafficking, drug smuggling, and the potential for transnational criminal organizations to exploit porous boundaries. These measures are fundamental to maintaining domestic safety and the integrity of our legal system.",
      "source": "target",
